  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Leaving Spain,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, has not yet accrued citations or public discussions across platforms. However, it maintains a strong commercial presence through listings on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, indicating potential interest in the work.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Leaving Spain,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, stems from a significant academic endeavor but currently has not generated public discourse as evidenced by the absence of mentions on platforms like Wikipedia, Reddit, and Bluesky. Such metrics suggest a limited outreach and engagement with broader societal discussions at this stage.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the lack of citations and community engagement, the work does have a notable commercial linkage, with listings on major book retail platforms, suggesting that it can attract readers primarily through commercial channels. This commercial potential could help elevate the book within targeted audiences interested in its themes.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Moreover, while scholarly impact through citations is absent, the inferred role of policy relevance indicates a connection to sustainability topics, as denoted by its association with one of the Sustainable Development Goals. Such elements could point to its utility in academic or policy-related discussions in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, while \"Leaving Spain\" has yet to make a substantive impact in terms of citations or online discourse, its commercial availability and inferred relevance to sustainability policy offer a foundation for potential growth. Enhancing visibility and engagement through targeted outreach may be beneficial in realizing the book's full impact in both academic and societal realms.</p>",
